<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1616,2038]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,152,503]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,1616,1643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Description:</emphasis>
Total length: 
<quantity box="[509,601,1617,1643]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1 mm</quantity>
; head height and width: 1.1 and 
<quantity box="[980,1070,1617,1643]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
, respectively; thorax height and width: 
<quantity box="[231,318,1653,1679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
and 1.7, mm respectively; Wing length: 
<quantity box="[783,873,1653,1679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[885,969,1652,1679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">MALE</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[984,1048,1653,1679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Head</emphasis>
: Spheroidal; eyes dull black lacking ommatrichia; vertex large and black with black ocelli located anterolaterally; ocellar triangle with two darkish, scarcely protuberant ocelli occupying 50% of vertex; clypeus black; (
<figureCitation box="[937,1006,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1239,1264]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,526,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[154,1434,525,1213]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–4. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, head, anterior view; (3) male, antenna; (4) Ogcodes porteri Schlinger, male, head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831700/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); occipital setae black; antenna black, flagellum with four black setae (
<figureCitation box="[518,585,1760,1787]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–4" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1239,1264]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,526,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[154,1434,525,1213]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–4. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, head, anterior view; (3) male, antenna; (4) Ogcodes porteri Schlinger, male, head, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831700/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[609,698,1761,1787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Thorax</emphasis>
: scutum shiny black, with large erected black pilosity continuous and sparsely distributed throughout (
<figureCitation box="[561,670,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Figs. 5–6</figureCitation>
); anepisternum, anepimeron, katepisterum, metasternum, meron and katatergite shiny black without hairs or with very scarce, short and black pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1132,1832,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); scutellum golden-yellow, with erected hairs of the same color (
<figureCitation box="[569,678,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Figs. 5–6</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[699,755,1869,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Legs</emphasis>
: mid legs missing as well as hind tibiae and tarsi due to manipulation of collector (see notes below); coxa and trochanter shiny black (
<figureCitation box="[991,1060,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); fore femora swollen with dense pilosity, with proximal area blackish and a golden-yellow sickle-shape marking; hind femora enlarged, not swollen, with few golden-yellow maculae distally; large and black hairs present (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1078,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); hind tibiae golden-yellow and thickened posteriorly, with short, yellow hairs distributed throughout; hind tarsi with golden-yellow color, excepting the fifth tarsus, which is darkish brown; claws darkish brown color (
<figureCitation box="[919,988,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1010,1075,152,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Wing</emphasis>
: with hyaline appearance, veins brown in color; cells c and sc with light brown color; veins M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[858,866,206,220]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">1</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[948,956,206,220]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">2</subScript>
absent; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1077,1085,206,220]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">4</subScript>
and CuA present, light brown; crossvein m–cu absent; halter golden-yellow; calypter rim shiny black and interior part is brownish (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1341,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1554,1579]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[195,1392,181,1528]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (6) male, left, wing venation; (7) male, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831706" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831706/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Triangular (
<figureCitation box="[349,417,261,288]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); tergite 1 completely shiny black with posterior thin white-yellow pale fascia; tergites 2–6 shiny black with posterior golden-yellow fasciae; the first three fasciae cover about one third of each segment, thickened toward the abdominal margins; fascia of tergite 4 more enlarged than those of tergites 1 and 2; golden-yellow fascia covering approximately 50% and 80% of tergites 5 and 6, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1094,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1611,1636]" captionTargetBox="[286,1262,202,1546]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[267,1321,181,1586]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (2) male, lateral view; (3) male, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831702/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); Abdominal fascia on tergites 2–5 not reaching the anterior margin; sclerites dull black with whitish fascia in the posterior margin; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1316,1436,404,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Genitalia:</emphasis>
partially everted (not dissected for this study); distal portion of aedeagus and gonopore rounded with a white mark; apex of the clasper brown (
<figureCitation box="[456,524,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1554,1579]" captionTargetBox="[195,1392,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[195,1392,181,1528]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Ogcodes kunkunche Barahona-Segovia sp. nov.: (6) male, left, wing venation; (7) male, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831706" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831706/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3831700" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3831700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3831700/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" startId="4.[151,264,1239,1264]" targetBox="[154,1434,526,1213]" targetPageId="4">
